## Structural interpretation

The main B10 mechanism can be summarized as:

```text
low noise
    -> channel/internal modes are rarely activated
    -> sustained capture is unlikely

intermediate noise
    -> activation and coherent persistence become possible
    -> sustained capture becomes likely

high noise
    -> first hit may still occur
    -> sustained capture is destroyed
```

This is why the result is described as **stochastic-resonance-like**. The phrase means that noise helps access a dynamical channel only within a finite range.

---

## Important caution

The figures in this directory should not be presented as calibrated nuclear-fusion plots.

In particular:

- the noise parameter is dimensionless within the reduced model;
- the model does not compute reaction rates;
- the model does not include Coulomb-barrier penetration;
- the model does not include quantum tunneling or nuclear potentials;
- the model does not predict fusion yield or real energy release.

The robust B10 claim is structural and model-level: sustained capture exhibits an intermediate-noise regime and a high-noise destruction regime under the adopted model and event definitions.

---

## Recommended wording

Preferred wording:

```text
stochastic-resonance-like finite-noise capture
```

```text
first hit versus sustained capture
```

```text
model-level finite-noise sustained-capture window
```

Avoid unqualified wording such as:

```text
B10 explains nuclear fusion
```

```text
B10 predicts fusion rates
```

```text
first hit means fusion
```

